  "response": "Here's a basic recipe for Gobi (Cauliflower) Manchurian:\n\nIngredients:\nFor Cauliflower Balls:\n- Cauliflower florets\n- Corn flour\n- All-purpose flour\n- Salt\n- Pepper\n- Water\n\nFor Manchurian Sauce:\n- Garlic\n- Ginger\n- Green chilies\n- Soy sauce\n- Chili sauce\n- Tomato ketchup\n- Oil\n- Salt\n\nSteps:\n1. Make batter with corn flour, all-purpose flour, salt, and pepper\n2. Coat cauliflower florets in batter\n3. Deep fry until golden brown\n\n4. For sauce:\n- Saut\u00e9 garlic, ginger, green chilies\n- Add soy sauce, chili sauce, ketchup\n- Mix well\n- Add fried cauliflower\n- Toss to coat\n\n5. Garnish with chopped spring onions\n\nTips:\n- Can use chicken instead of cauliflower\n- Adjust spice levels to taste\n- Serve hot as appetizer or side dish\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any part of the recipe?",
